      "note_no": "61",
      "note": "Since it is obviously impossible to attribute to a prophet the levity of scoffing (Baghawi), the meaning of the above phrase seems to be this: \"If you consider us ignorant because of what we believe and are doing, we consider you ignorant because of your refusal to acknowledge the truth and your readiness to expose yourselves to God's punishment\" (Zamakhshari and, in a shorter form, Baghawi). Hence my interpolation of the words \"and your ignorance\"."
